      "reasoning": "The mutation changes '>=' to '>' in the boundary check at line 88. However, 'batch_channel' is computed as tid / threads_per_channel, where threads_per_channel = blockDim.x * gridDim.x / (batch_size * channels). Since integer division truncates toward zero, batch_channel can only take values from 0 to (batch_size * channels - 1) when tid ranges from 0 to (batch_size * channels * threads_per_channel - 1). The condition 'batch_channel >= batch_size * channels' in the original code is already impossible to satisfy because batch_channel is always less than batch_size * channels. Changing it to '>' makes no difference - both conditions are always false for valid inputs. The only way to trigger this condition would be if threads_per_channel = 0, but that's already caught by an earlier return statement. Therefore, this mutation is truly equivalent under all input values.",
